FT  28 MAY 94 / Finance and the Family: S G Warburg doubles profit - At a
Glance
SG Warburg, the investment bank, this week reported record pre-tax profits
for the year to March 31, reflecting sustained growth in commission and fee
income from advisory and underwriting activities.
At Pounds 297m, profits were double the comparable Pounds 148.2m for the
previous year, on total operating income of Pounds 1.04bn (Pounds 715.8m).
'The business, in common with the industry, has had a good year,' said Lord
Cairns, chief executive. However, he added: 'It could prove to be a peak
year in the economic cycle.'
